"a.笨重的，笨拙的 【英】 adj. 笨重的，笨拙的(unwi eldy or clumsy) 【考】 反义词：gossamer(轻 而薄的); lively(轻的); ethereal(轻的); slight(轻的); vibrant(活泼的); briskly(活泼的) 【记】 ponder(重量)+ous→ 有重量的→笨重的 【例】 The ponderous elephant plodded toward the river. adj. 笨重的(因重量或体积太大而难以操作或不灵便的) 【记】pond重量, er, ous多－有很多重量的－笨重的 【反】gossamer(adj 轻而薄的); lively(adj 轻快活泼的); ethereal(adj 轻的)slight(adj 轻微的); vibrant(adj 轻快活泼的); brisk(adj 轻快的); 【记】源自pound 重量单位，音：磅，属于外来语；音：胖得要死→笨重 ponderous (adj.)  c.1400, ""thick;"" early 15c., ""heavy, weighty, clumsy,"" from Latin ponderosus ""of great weight; full of meaning,"" from pondus (genitive ponderis) ""weight"" (see pound (n.1)). Meaning ""tedious"" is first recorded 1704. Related: Ponderously; ponderousness."
